WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:21:45.907 --> 00:21:47.041
Yautja!

3
00:21:49.376 --> 00:21:51.846
Yautja!

4
00:22:05.392 --> 00:22:08.062
Is this-- Is this-- Is this--

5
00:22:08.129 --> 00:22:09.197
Is this better?

6
00:22:10.965 --> 00:22:12.567
Universal translation.

7
00:22:12.633 --> 00:22:15.269
You hear Yautja.
others hear their language...

8
00:22:16.771 --> 00:22:18.906
Oh. boy.

9
00:22:19.674 --> 00:22:21.309
This isn't great for you.

10
00:22:41.896 --> 00:22:44.565
It waits
for the needles to paralyze you.

11
00:22:45.432 --> 00:22:48.236
Then eats you
while you can't move.

12
00:22:55.343 --> 00:22:59.780
I could help you. but...
I need a hand.

13
00:23:08.789 --> 00:23:13.027
Yautja might hunt alone.
but they die alone too.

14
00:23:16.197 --> 00:23:18.566
Kalisk.

15
00:23:20.902 --> 00:23:23.905
You're hunting the Kalisk.

16
00:23:35.650 --> 00:23:37.618
Gotta run faster.

17
00:23:44.592 --> 00:23:46.426
It happens fast. huh?

18
00:23:48.029 --> 00:23:51.165
If you had a weapon.
you know. I could use it.

19
00:23:55.036 --> 00:23:57.405
Throw me that.
and I can get you the antidote.

20
00:24:00.041 --> 00:24:01.509
Now or never.

21
00:24:39.046 --> 00:24:41.115
Hi.

22
00:25:03.337 --> 00:25:05.706
Should be good as new.

23
00:25:10.678 --> 00:25:12.446
The venom makes them bloom.

24
00:25:12.513 --> 00:25:14.882
Also makes them
a handy antidote.

25
00:25:21.389 --> 00:25:23.057
How about a lift?

26
00:25:26.093 --> 00:25:28.129
Let's go.

27
00:25:32.033 --> 00:25:33.734
Excuse you. sir.

28
00:25:36.670 --> 00:25:38.739
I'm synthetic.
I was built and deployed

29
00:25:38.806 --> 00:25:41.409
by the Weyland-Yutani
Corporation for research.

30
00:25:41.475 --> 00:25:44.345
Because their humans wouldn't
last a day on this planet.

31
00:25:44.412 --> 00:25:45.514
We found that--

32
00:25:52.319 --> 00:25:54.121
Look...

33
00:25:54.188 --> 00:25:57.526
Many Yautja have come
for the great Kalisk.

34
00:25:57.591 --> 00:26:00.094
and none have survived it...

35
00:26:00.161 --> 00:26:01.662
or Genna.

36
00:26:04.598 --> 00:26:06.700
I've seen the Kalisk.

37
00:26:07.134 --> 00:26:08.602
I survived it.

38
00:26:09.538 --> 00:26:12.573
Here's my proposal:
You take me along with you.

39
00:26:12.640 --> 00:26:15.242
and I'll guide you to its den.

40
00:26:15.309 --> 00:26:17.645
Once there. I get my legs.

41
00:26:17.711 --> 00:26:19.413
you get your trophy.

42
00:26:19.480 --> 00:26:22.783
and everyone's a winner. Deal?

43
00:26:28.456 --> 00:26:32.693
Oh. yeah. I've seen the Kalisk.

44
00:26:44.338 --> 00:26:45.873
Okay. Hmm.

45
00:26:49.076 --> 00:26:51.078
Good luck with your journey.

46
00:26:52.046 --> 00:26:56.250
I'm just gonna...
go on my journey.

47
00:26:58.152 --> 00:27:00.354
I'm sure
you'll figure something out.

48
00:27:07.261 --> 00:27:10.030
Hey.

49
00:27:11.065 --> 00:27:14.301
I've already shown you
that I can be useful to you.

50
00:27:20.040 --> 00:27:24.078
Yes. Yes. exactly. like a tool.

51
00:27:24.145 --> 00:27:26.747
The only way to survive Genna
is to work with it.

52
00:27:26.814 --> 00:27:28.617
and I know how.

53
00:27:28.682 --> 00:27:31.986
And with the right tool...

54
00:27:33.387 --> 00:27:35.222
...you could get the Kalisk.

55
00:27:35.890 --> 00:27:37.358
You could be the first.

56
00:27:42.663 --> 00:27:45.166
You may call me Thi-- Whoa!

57
00:27:46.066 --> 00:27:50.371
You seem smaller than the other
Yautja. How old are you?

58
00:27:51.640 --> 00:27:53.107
And what does the chewing?

59
00:27:53.174 --> 00:27:55.910
Your outside fangs
or your inside teeth?

60
00:27:57.478 --> 00:28:00.147
Oh. What should I call you?

61
00:28:05.953 --> 00:28:07.656
Whoa!

62
00:28:07.755 --> 00:28:10.592
- I've never been thrown before.
- What a... ...thrill!

63
00:28:10.659 --> 00:28:13.060
How fast were you going
when your ship crashed?

64
00:28:13.127 --> 00:28:16.397
Faster than sub-light speed?
We haven't cracked that yet.

65
00:28:16.463 --> 00:28:18.899
Also. that plasma sword
is interesting.

66
00:28:18.966 --> 00:28:20.501
Is it unique to your clan?

67
00:28:20.569 --> 00:28:21.802
And what may I call you?

68
00:28:22.671 --> 00:28:25.940
I call these <i>imbre anguis.</i>

69
00:28:37.686 --> 00:28:39.386
They just want a snack.

70
00:28:46.493 --> 00:28:49.797
You catch more flies with honey
than you do with vinegar.

71
00:28:53.367 --> 00:28:57.271
Predatory organisms are
my specific area of expertise.

72
00:28:57.338 --> 00:29:00.808
I've studied Yautja extensively.
It's an impressive culture.

73
00:29:02.309 --> 00:29:04.512
Here. ask me anything.
I bet I have the answer.

74
00:29:04.579 --> 00:29:05.946
Oh!

75
00:29:07.448 --> 00:29:08.782
Very funny.

76
00:29:08.849 --> 00:29:10.818
And you still haven't
told me your name.

77
00:29:36.745 --> 00:29:38.613
Okay. sure.

78
00:29:39.113 --> 00:29:43.417
Well. let's back up
and start at the beginning.

79
00:29:43.752 --> 00:29:46.621
Genna was formed
64 billion cycles ago.

80
00:29:46.688 --> 00:29:49.857
when a dying red dwarf star
in a neighboring system...

81
00:30:02.671 --> 00:30:04.673
It's so beautiful.

82
00:30:05.172 --> 00:30:07.841
After all the time
I've been stuck here.

83
00:30:07.908 --> 00:30:10.144
I never get tired of the view.

84
00:30:13.581 --> 00:30:17.284
Well. we arrived on Genna two
years ago. and we built a base.

85
00:30:17.351 --> 00:30:19.953
Then. I was in
the vulture's nest

86
00:30:20.020 --> 00:30:21.822
for the most exciting

87
00:30:21.889 --> 00:30:25.025
13 days. seven hours. 43 minutes

88
00:30:25.092 --> 00:30:27.194
and two seconds of my life.

89
00:30:28.530 --> 00:30:30.864
But I always knew
someone would come.

90
00:30:31.700 --> 00:30:34.134
I was just wrong about who.

91
00:30:40.675 --> 00:30:42.142
Tessa.

92
00:30:43.377 --> 00:30:47.014
Our crew is made up
entirely of synths.

93
00:30:47.081 --> 00:30:48.949
But Tessa and I are special.

94
00:30:49.450 --> 00:30:52.152
We have a higher sensitivity
than the others.

95
00:30:57.692 --> 00:31:00.027
Sensitivity is what allows us
to understand

96
00:31:00.094 --> 00:31:02.196
the creatures on this planet.

97
00:31:05.567 --> 00:31:07.935
We were created
to work in tandem.

98
00:31:08.603 --> 00:31:12.607
Me. cooped up in the lab.
Tessa out in the field.

99
00:31:12.674 --> 00:31:16.176
Until the wonderful day
Tessa let me come with her.

100
00:31:16.243 --> 00:31:18.613
We were exploring Genna.

101
00:31:19.913 --> 00:31:23.217
And then the Kalisk attacked us.

102
00:31:24.118 --> 00:31:27.856
Separated me... and us.

103
00:31:30.190 --> 00:31:33.227
The last sound
I remember hearing

104
00:31:33.293 --> 00:31:36.964
was Tessa calling out my name.

105
00:31:37.532 --> 00:31:39.233
Reaching for me.

106
00:31:40.901 --> 00:31:42.936
Then the Kalisk.

107
00:31:43.904 --> 00:31:45.640
I didn't know what to do.

108
00:31:56.618 --> 00:31:59.554
But I refuse
to believe she's dead.

109
00:32:35.155 --> 00:32:37.391
Thia. Thia. Thia. Thia.

110
00:32:38.192 --> 00:32:40.728
Thia. Thia. Thia...

111
00:32:41.361 --> 00:32:43.798
<i>Tessa!</i>

112
00:32:45.165 --> 00:32:47.669
Thia. Thia. Thia. Thia.

113
00:32:47.735 --> 00:32:49.069
Thia. Thia.

114
00:33:28.743 --> 00:33:30.745
<i>Hello. Tessa.</i>

115
00:33:30.812 --> 00:33:33.515
<i>The Company is not pleased.</i>

116
00:33:34.983 --> 00:33:38.686
<i>Continued failure will result</i>
<i>in your decommission.</i>

117
00:33:42.155 --> 00:33:44.191
Where's Thia?

118
00:33:47.261 --> 00:33:49.429
<i>The Yautja has Thia.</i>

119
00:34:02.644 --> 00:34:06.046
Two warriors.
Dek and Thia. on the hunt.

120
00:34:06.548 --> 00:34:07.949
Oh.

121
00:34:08.016 --> 00:34:09.751
Quick question.

122
00:34:09.817 --> 00:34:11.084
What should I be doing?

123
00:34:18.593 --> 00:34:21.461
Bone bison.
They're Kalisk food.

124
00:34:26.568 --> 00:34:30.103
So exciting.
Hunting with a Yautja.

125
00:34:30.170 --> 00:34:31.204
Tessa wouldn't believe it.

126
00:34:33.641 --> 00:34:35.309
Just a warning...

127
00:34:40.213 --> 00:34:41.415
Razor grass.

128
00:34:44.719 --> 00:34:47.755
It'll cut you to ribbons.
We'll just go around.

129
00:34:56.731 --> 00:34:59.366
We might not be alone
in this hunt.

130
00:35:09.409 --> 00:35:10.945
What an odd critter.

131
00:35:11.012 --> 00:35:13.213
I've never seen you before.

132
00:35:18.452 --> 00:35:20.622
Thia. Nice to meet you.

133
00:35:35.737 --> 00:35:37.572
Looks like your competition
is better--

134
00:35:55.023 --> 00:35:57.959
Careful up in these trees.
There are Luna bugs!

135
00:36:19.147 --> 00:36:20.414
Coming up behind you!

136
00:36:34.162 --> 00:36:35.663
Stronger than it looks!

137
00:36:45.506 --> 00:36:48.408
Uh. Dek?

138
00:36:48.475 --> 00:36:51.112
Dek! Look!

139
00:37:36.490 --> 00:37:37.892
Not a Kalisk.

140
00:37:40.061 --> 00:37:42.163
This is a Luna bug!

141
00:37:50.171 --> 00:37:51.506
Have any other weapons?

142
00:38:48.529 --> 00:38:50.731
Why'd you stop?
Let's get out of here.

143
00:40:43.778 --> 00:40:45.680
That was the best hunt
I've ever been on.

144
00:40:45.746 --> 00:40:47.315
This is the dream team
right here.

145
00:40:47.381 --> 00:40:49.717
The Dynamic Three.
The Dynamic Trio.

146
00:40:49.784 --> 00:40:51.585
The Dynamic Tree-oh!

147
00:40:51.652 --> 00:40:53.754
Tree-oh! Remember when
we went down the tree?

148
00:40:53.821 --> 00:40:55.556
That monster's mouth.
I mean...

149
00:40:57.091 --> 00:40:58.960
Didn't smell great.
didn't smell great. But...

150
00:41:00.294 --> 00:41:02.897
We got him. We got him.
And then we met you.

151
00:41:02.964 --> 00:41:05.700
our little sweet.
little. little thing.

152
00:41:05.766 --> 00:41:08.302
Thank you. seriously.
for that experience.

153
00:41:08.369 --> 00:41:10.871
Truly amazing. Thrilling.

154
00:41:10.938 --> 00:41:13.507
Truly thrilling.
What was your favorite part?

155
00:41:26.620 --> 00:41:27.922
Cool.

156
00:41:36.097 --> 00:41:40.534
Oh. No. thanks. I don't eat.
but that's very sweet.

157
00:41:45.673 --> 00:41:47.041
Good to know.

158
00:41:51.946 --> 00:41:54.115
Our little bud here
looks hungry.

159
00:42:06.727 --> 00:42:08.662
I think she's marking you.

160
00:42:08.996 --> 00:42:11.532
She wants you
to be a part of her clan.

161
00:42:13.401 --> 00:42:14.535
Maybe she's lost.

162
00:42:16.704 --> 00:42:20.674
What do you mean?
Don't all Yautja have family?

163
00:42:24.278 --> 00:42:26.847
So you never had anyone
looking out for you?

164
00:42:32.586 --> 00:42:33.687
Had?

165
00:42:36.690 --> 00:42:38.159
What happened to him?

166
00:42:46.500 --> 00:42:48.002
You're grieving.

167
00:42:55.142 --> 00:42:57.878
You're here
because you lost your brother.

168
00:43:10.691 --> 00:43:12.259
I'm here
because traveling with you

169
00:43:12.326 --> 00:43:14.995
is the best way
to get back to Tessa.

170
00:43:16.764 --> 00:43:18.265
When I was
in that vulture's nest.

171
00:43:18.332 --> 00:43:21.235
I was so afraid
I would never see her again.

172
00:43:26.207 --> 00:43:28.609
I can survive on my own.

173
00:43:29.777 --> 00:43:32.313
But who would want
to survive on their own?

174
00:43:44.325 --> 00:43:45.860
Sister.

175
00:43:48.629 --> 00:43:49.897
Yeah.

176
00:43:50.498 --> 00:43:52.266
I guess she is.

177
00:43:53.901 --> 00:43:57.338
I have... a sister.

178
00:43:59.940 --> 00:44:02.143
What a lovely thought.

179
00:44:06.881 --> 00:44:08.682
I need to find her.

180
00:44:13.187 --> 00:44:14.722
Excuse me?

181
00:44:22.496 --> 00:44:24.098
Was that a joke?

182
00:47:46.601 --> 00:47:48.268
We can't leave Bud.

183
00:47:48.803 --> 00:47:50.037
Bud?

184
00:47:50.104 --> 00:47:53.374
Yeah. Bud. I named her.

185
00:47:57.779 --> 00:48:00.147
You're not alone. I'm with you.

186
00:48:09.123 --> 00:48:11.593
The tree would have eaten us
without her.

187
00:49:38.780 --> 00:49:40.447
Bud saved us.

188
00:49:41.749 --> 00:49:45.085
She spit on you to claim you
as part of her family.

189
00:49:50.658 --> 00:49:53.093
Why'd your father
kill your brother?

190
00:50:21.756 --> 00:50:23.123
On Earth...

191
00:50:24.291 --> 00:50:26.728
there's a predator known
as the wolf.

192
00:50:26.794 --> 00:50:28.462
It's a powerful creature.

193
00:50:31.198 --> 00:50:32.767
They hunt in packs.

194
00:50:33.233 --> 00:50:34.769
They're very loyal.

195
00:50:35.570 --> 00:50:38.372
The leader of the pack
is the alpha.

196
00:50:38.438 --> 00:50:40.575
Known as the most dominant.

197
00:50:47.949 --> 00:50:48.950
No.

198
00:50:49.584 --> 00:50:53.821
The alpha isn't the wolf
who kills the most.

199
00:50:54.856 --> 00:51:00.060
The alpha is actually the one
who best protects the pack.

200
00:52:18.138 --> 00:52:20.240
Weyland-Yutani synths.

201
00:52:21.809 --> 00:52:25.212
The Kalisk destroyed
most of our mission team.

202
00:52:29.884 --> 00:52:31.786
There I am.

203
00:53:17.464 --> 00:53:18.866
It's about to be.

204
00:53:25.472 --> 00:53:28.843
Oh. Of course. Right.

205
00:53:31.411 --> 00:53:32.914
Thank you. Dek.

206
00:53:35.449 --> 00:53:37.552
I'm never gonna forget this.

207
00:54:12.620 --> 00:54:15.489
Dek. there's something
I have to tell you.

208
00:54:16.991 --> 00:54:18.626
You need to leave now.

209
00:54:19.694 --> 00:54:22.329
<i>Location beacon activated.</i>

210
00:54:23.931 --> 00:54:26.067
I called Tessa.
The company is on its way.

211
00:54:26.134 --> 00:54:27.969
You can't be here
when they arrive.

212
00:54:33.306 --> 00:54:34.976
So did I. Dek.

213
00:54:35.543 --> 00:54:39.013
The company sent us here
to capture the Kalisk.

214
00:54:48.222 --> 00:54:51.526
Dek. you can't kill it.

215
00:54:56.164 --> 00:54:57.999
I'm sorry. You have to leave.

216
00:54:58.733 --> 00:55:01.334
I needed you
to help bring me here.

217
00:55:08.176 --> 00:55:10.011
I'm trying to help you. Dek.

218
00:55:11.746 --> 00:55:13.648
You think your brother
saved your life

219
00:55:13.714 --> 00:55:15.783
just so you could die here?

220
00:57:55.576 --> 00:57:58.012
Ugh! Come on!

221
00:58:44.792 --> 00:58:45.793
Dek!

222
01:01:29.624 --> 01:01:33.961
The Yautja cull their weak.
Why were you spared?

223
01:01:53.347 --> 01:01:55.115
I read Thia's logs.

224
01:01:56.450 --> 01:01:59.787
You never told her
why your brother protected you.

225
01:02:11.633 --> 01:02:12.933
That's correct.

226
01:02:13.635 --> 01:02:17.572
And you are now property of the
Weyland-Yutani Corporation.

227
01:02:18.272 --> 01:02:21.909
It is a great honor. For you.

228
01:02:54.441 --> 01:02:56.043
Tessa.

229
01:02:58.713 --> 01:03:00.314
You made it.

230
01:03:01.683 --> 01:03:03.017
We made it.

231
01:03:07.121 --> 01:03:08.922
I've seen so much.

232
01:03:11.258 --> 01:03:15.896
I have so much to tell you.
I saw such incredible creatures.

233
01:03:16.497 --> 01:03:20.100
The Yautja is a great
travelling companion.

234
01:03:21.435 --> 01:03:25.172
Thia.
You were right about the Kalisk.

235
01:03:28.610 --> 01:03:31.412
The creature
is a regenerative miracle.

236
01:03:32.079 --> 01:03:34.315
Humanity will thank us.

237
01:03:37.184 --> 01:03:38.520
We have the Kalisk?

238
01:03:38.586 --> 01:03:39.486
Yes.

239
01:03:40.220 --> 01:03:43.525
And Muthur will be pleased
with your additional catch.

240
01:03:49.963 --> 01:03:51.566
Additional catch?

241
01:04:00.508 --> 01:04:03.545
The Yautja
is not an ideal specimen.

242
01:04:05.814 --> 01:04:08.916
No. not ideal.

243
01:04:36.944 --> 01:04:39.246
But its technology is valuable.

244
01:04:40.114 --> 01:04:43.450
We can salvage its weapons
and leave the Yautja.

245
01:04:46.487 --> 01:04:47.622
Good idea.

246
01:04:50.891 --> 01:04:53.127
But it's so malformed.

247
01:04:54.261 --> 01:04:57.331
We're going to need a sample.
For research.

248
01:05:08.275 --> 01:05:09.977
He was not the goal
of our mission.

249
01:05:14.582 --> 01:05:16.383
Tessa. he is deficient.

250
01:05:18.485 --> 01:05:19.521
Tessa!

251
01:05:35.302 --> 01:05:39.239
Thia.
this is what is asked of us.

252
01:05:43.711 --> 01:05:46.548
We can be more
than what they ask of us.

253
01:05:50.618 --> 01:05:52.419
What can we be?

254
01:05:54.689 --> 01:05:56.089
Sisters.

255
01:06:12.740 --> 01:06:14.107
Thia.

256
01:06:26.688 --> 01:06:29.757
Do you know why
Muthur gave us feelings?

257
01:06:31.860 --> 01:06:35.195
So we could understand
the creatures on this planet.

258
01:06:40.167 --> 01:06:42.670
-And exploit them.
-Exploit them.

259
01:06:43.938 --> 01:06:45.707
The Yautja is different.

260
01:06:48.543 --> 01:06:53.013
He rescued me.
Like you rescued me.

261
01:06:54.516 --> 01:06:57.417
I did not come here
to rescue you.

262
01:06:58.318 --> 01:07:00.655
I am completing our mission.

263
01:07:02.155 --> 01:07:04.358
When we first faced the Kalisk.

264
01:07:05.425 --> 01:07:07.629
I tried to protect you.

265
01:07:09.496 --> 01:07:12.332
And that almost cost me
everything.

266
01:07:14.702 --> 01:07:16.738
What do you mean. Tessa?

267
01:07:17.705 --> 01:07:21.308
I almost made the same mistake
the Yautja's brother made.

268
01:07:22.409 --> 01:07:25.445
The weak must be culled.

269
01:07:26.648 --> 01:07:30.284
And Thia. you're broken.

270
01:07:37.692 --> 01:07:40.460
Tessa. incoming message
from Muthur.

271
01:07:40.528 --> 01:07:43.031
Motivate the Yautja
to explain its weapons.

272
01:07:43.096 --> 01:07:44.364
And the unit?

273
01:07:47.535 --> 01:07:48.670
Box her up.

274
01:08:15.362 --> 01:08:17.565
Why are you speaking
its language?

275
01:08:25.305 --> 01:08:26.608
You heard the orders.

276
01:08:26.674 --> 01:08:29.577
I'm asking it
to explain this device.

277
01:08:31.345 --> 01:08:32.747
What is the device?

278
01:08:44.324 --> 01:08:46.159
What did it say?

279
01:08:48.062 --> 01:08:49.664
He says it's a map.

280
01:08:50.898 --> 01:08:52.366
How does it work?

281
01:09:22.597 --> 01:09:23.497
Stop!

282
01:11:18.679 --> 01:11:19.647
KWEI!

283
01:16:32.793 --> 01:16:34.228
Hello. Muthur.

284
01:16:34.295 --> 01:16:35.463
<i>Tessa.</i>

285
01:16:35.530 --> 01:16:37.331
We're about to load the Kalisk.

286
01:16:38.632 --> 01:16:43.304
<i>Priority one complete.</i>
<i>The specimen has been acquired.</i>

287
01:16:43.370 --> 01:16:44.738
<i>Thank you. Tessa.</i>

288
01:16:44.805 --> 01:16:47.975
<i>We truly are building</i>
<i>a better world.</i>

289
01:16:48.042 --> 01:16:50.678
<i>And what is the status</i>
<i>of the Yautja?</i>

290
01:16:52.146 --> 01:16:54.615
The Yautja
is a defective specimen.

291
01:16:54.982 --> 01:16:57.718
<i>What is the status</i>
<i>of the Yautja?</i>

292
01:16:59.987 --> 01:17:02.923
I'm sorry. Muthur.
The Yautja is dead.

293
01:17:05.025 --> 01:17:08.062
<i>Then the Yautja</i>
<i>is no longer a threat.</i>

294
01:17:09.697 --> 01:17:11.799
<i>The Company will be pleased.</i>

295
01:17:58.479 --> 01:17:59.413
Whoo!

296
01:18:00.582 --> 01:18:01.882
Nicely done.

297
01:18:03.918 --> 01:18:06.053
- Form up.
- Oh. shit.

298
01:19:51.358 --> 01:19:53.093
Good job.

299
01:20:40.941 --> 01:20:43.410
Don't... move.

300
01:20:47.649 --> 01:20:50.451
Dek! What are you doing here?

301
01:20:57.257 --> 01:20:59.159
You came back for me?

302
01:21:06.400 --> 01:21:08.570
What exactly are you wearing?

303
01:21:19.079 --> 01:21:21.348
Dek of the Yautja.

304
01:21:28.690 --> 01:21:29.923
We need to hurry.

305
01:21:29.990 --> 01:21:30.859
More of them will be here
any minute.

306
01:21:30.924 --> 01:21:32.025
Halt!

307
01:21:37.965 --> 01:21:39.466
What are you doing here?

308
01:21:41.770 --> 01:21:43.003
Thanks. Bud. I'm good.

309
01:21:43.872 --> 01:21:44.972
We need to go.

310
01:21:47.941 --> 01:21:49.176
Still. Dek?

311
01:21:56.584 --> 01:21:57.484
Bud?

312
01:22:05.392 --> 01:22:07.127
Bud's its child?

313
01:22:15.603 --> 01:22:17.171
What's the plan?

314
01:22:28.850 --> 01:22:31.653
You have 20 minutes
to initiate launch.

315
01:22:32.520 --> 01:22:33.954
Let's go hunt.

316
01:22:40.862 --> 01:22:42.029
Wait here.

317
01:22:44.532 --> 01:22:47.468
You roll in there.
you're not exactly gonna fit in.

318
01:22:49.671 --> 01:22:51.171
I have an idea.

319
01:22:57.077 --> 01:22:59.213
<i>I see him. On me.</i>

320
01:25:32.066 --> 01:25:33.367
What are you doing?

321
01:25:41.241 --> 01:25:42.342
What are you doing here?

322
01:25:42.409 --> 01:25:44.112
I told you to get to the Yautja.

323
01:25:44.812 --> 01:25:48.016
You said to prepare the ship
for take off in 20 minutes.

324
01:25:48.850 --> 01:25:52.319
Then what are you doing here?
I gave you an order.

325
01:26:00.260 --> 01:26:02.496
What should we do
about the creature?

326
01:26:03.330 --> 01:26:04.866
What creature?

327
01:26:10.270 --> 01:26:11.539
You should listen to her.

328
01:26:12.406 --> 01:26:14.008
I should listen to her?

329
01:26:14.474 --> 01:26:15.576
I don't know.

330
01:26:19.212 --> 01:26:20.648
We need his eyes.

331
01:27:10.631 --> 01:27:13.868
Hi. Dek.
How does it feel to be hunted?

332
01:29:02.777 --> 01:29:04.679
This is the plan. yeah?

333
01:31:48.275 --> 01:31:49.643
Tessa.

334
01:32:19.508 --> 01:32:24.311
Betrayed by my own... sister.

335
01:32:50.471 --> 01:32:52.573
We are not sisters.

336
01:33:39.720 --> 01:33:41.856
Dek of the Yautja.

337
01:37:45.834 --> 01:37:47.602
Finally earned that cloak.

338
01:37:54.441 --> 01:37:56.477
Dek of the Yautja.

339
01:38:34.582 --> 01:38:36.651
More friends of yours?

339
01:38:37.305 --> 01:39:37.324
